      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite; all CFD routines traceable to validated software baseline under 21 CFR Part 11-compatible configuration management.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under a qualified software environment with full audit trail. Version control, change control, and regression test suite documented. Achieved level meets MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy testing on canonical flows (Taylor-Couette, lid-driven cavity) confirms expected spatial and temporal convergence rates for the turbulence and hemolysis sub-models.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed on simplified rotating-channel and pipe-flow benchmarks. Second-order spatial accuracy confirmed. Hemolysis power-law integration verified against analytical solutions. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI on three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% on finest mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study conducted at representative operating point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM). GCI for normalized hemolysis index = 3.2% on the fine mesh (9.4 M cells). Discretization error budget included in Monte Carlo UQ propagation. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid viscosity, hematocrit, temperature, pump speed) documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments conducted with bovine blood at 37 °C, Hct 33±2%, speeds 2000–3500 RPM. Simulation boundary conditions replicate experimental values; deviations in viscosity (±3%) bounded and propagated through UQ. Test condition fidelity confirmed at gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E_rel) between predicted and measured normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) at each operating point; mean E_rel < 20% and all predictions within Monte Carlo 95th-percentile band.",
      "rationale": "Across 5 operating conditions, mean E_rel = 14.7%. All experimental NIH measurements fall within the Monte Carlo 95% prediction interval. Systematic over-prediction at low speed (2000 RPM) noted but within acceptable tolerance. Output comparison gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH and absolute plasma-free hemoglobin rise rate) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint; linkage to patient harm pathway documented.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is NIH expressed in mg/dL/min, directly correlated with chronic hemolysis risk in VAD patients. Secondary QoI is shear stress exposure time integral. Both QoIs are the direct regulatory endpoints for FDA 510(k) hemolysis assessment. Relevance gradation 4 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same FDA generic pump geometry, blood analogue properties, and operating envelope as the COU; no geometric surrogates employed.",
      "rationale": "Validation data sourced from FDA-commissioned experiments on the identical generic centrifugal pump geometry used in the COU. Operating conditions span the full clinical envelope. No surrogate geometries or scaled models used. Validation-to-COU relevance gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual < 1e-5 for all equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%; hemolysis integral monitored for iteration-to-iteration variation < 0.5%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to scaled residuals below 1e-5. Mass imbalance 0.004%. Hemolysis index variation between final 500 iterations < 0.3%. Solver error contribution bounded and included in overall uncertainty budget. Gradation 3 requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition application, mesh topology, and hemolysis model parameter assignment independently verified against simulation protocol.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup conducted by second qualified CFD analyst. Boundary conditions, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), and hemolysis power-law coefficients (Giersiepen et al.) verified. One minor discrepancy in inlet turbulence intensity corrected prior to final runs. Use error gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection justified by physics arguments and prior literature; alternative model forms evaluated on a representative case.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on demonstrated superior performance in rotating machinery flows. Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen) compared against Taskin model on 6 L/min case; NIH predictions within 8% of each other. Model form uncertainty included in the Monte Carlo UQ ensemble. Gradation 4 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and operating input parameters assigned probability distributions informed by experimental measurement uncertainty; distributions propagated via comprehensive Monte Carlo sampling (N ≥ 1000 runs).",
      "rationale": "Probability distributions assigned to six primary inputs: blood dynamic viscosity (normal, CV=3%), hematocrit (normal, CV=6%), pump rotational speed (uniform ±15 RPM), inlet flow rate (normal, CV=2%), and hemolysis power-law exponent and coefficient (log-normal, based on Giersiepen scatter). Monte Carlo ensemble of 1200 CFD-surrogate evaluations propagated through a validated response surface. Comprehensive UQ coverage documented. Model inputs gradation 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements obtained from at least 3 independent blood donors per operating condition; inter-sample variability reported.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental dataset includes n=5 independent bovine blood samples per operating condition. Inter-sample coefficient of variation for NIH ranges from 8% to 17% across conditions. Sample variability incorporated into validation comparison uncertainty bands. Test samples gradation 3 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (viscosity, density, hematocrit) match experimental conditions within stated measurement uncertainty; any systematic offsets documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Simulation fluid properties set to match experimental blood analogue measurements. Viscosity offset of 1.8% identified between nominal and measured values; propagated through UQ. Density matched to within 0.5%. Hematocrit equivalency confirmed via pre- and post-experiment measurements. Equivalency gradation 3 met."
    }
